Description: Sub-rectangular mottled black steatite stamp seal with protuding suspension loop on the back; the side of the seal has an incised line running around its edge; the face is framed by a border and shows in the lower half a long-horned mammal, and in the upper half a bird with a circular dot (sun/star?) in the top-left corner (top-right when stamped).
Curator's comments: Greville John Chester acquired objects from throughout the Middle East and Egypt with little to no documentation on specific object's origins existing.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Rev Greville John Chester
